6:
I just think it's odd, is all. Kyrie
choosing to go back home all on her
own.
9:
Perhaps she saw the error of her
ways and finally decided to return
home to her parents.
22:
That was a little TOO fast—what
happened?
27:
I see... So your dad saw you fiddling
around with a rifle, huh?
30:
And I was being so careful not to get
spotted too!
34:
And your dad had no idea that you
were such an, er, enthusiast, did he?
35:
Were you able to talk things through
with him?
40:
Ngh... No! He was so angry that I
couldn't even get a word in!
So I... I...
46:
So basically nothing has changed
since last time?
49:
I'm gonna do everything I can to get
his approval!
50:
And to do that, I need to get better!
I'm gonna work on my
marksmanship all day until I'm a pro!
53:
But... Where would I even do that? I
need a place where I can just let
loose, you know?
59: Strange as she is, the kid's got talent.
63:
Hehe, I try. But I just wish Father
would see it that way too.
66:
Your precious daughter isn't frail
and helpless! She can look after
herself!
70: He'd probably faint on the spot.
80: R-roger! Leave it to me, I'll handle it!
85:
Careful, Kyrie! Don't go out too far
forward!
88:
I'll be okay! I'm in tip-top shape—no
monster's gonna get the best of me!
104: I… I'll shoot that monster down!
112:
Damn, it's faster than it looks. Take it
out quickly!
116:
G-got it! But, I… I can't seem to land
a single shot!
126:
I have to hurry and help Light! But…
but I…
129:
What do I do? What if... What if I miss
my shot? Or hit Light by accident?
133: I... Augh, I can't do it!
136:
It's all right, Kyrie! Trust in yourself. I
believe in you.
141:
Light, I… I want to, but… my hands are
trembling!
145:
Clear your mind! There's no need to
think!
154:
Close your eyes and shoot! Don't
think about anything or anyone else,
and just pull the trigger!
160:
What are you saying, Light? If she
misses—
172:
Ahhh!
Too many people are telling me
what to do! I don't know anymore!
176:
That's it, it's time to take a shot… I'm
pulling the trigger now, okay?!
197:
*sob* Liiiiight!
I'm so, so sorry! I got carried away,
and you—
201: I wasn't worried for a moment.
204:
As long as you trusted yourself to
pull the trigger, I knew your shot
would land precisely where it
needed to.
209: Is that really how it works?
212:
For those who possess such
incredible talents, it does... from time
to time.
215:
But there may be battles ahead
where we can't rely on faith alone. It
is thus important to remain calm
and control one's—Kyrie?
220:
Incredible... talent?
You really think so? I'm not just
imagining it, right?
222:
T-to tell you the truth… The thought
did occur to me a bit. Maybe I AM a
sharpshooting genius! Hehe!
223:
So it's settled! I'm going to help
everyone out from now on—I'll prove
myself to father once and for all!
230: I can't wait for our next adventure!
